# TRIGONOMETRY LAWS and IDENTITIES
- Tangent Identities
            tanθ = sinθ / cosθ
            cotθ = cosθ / sinθ

- Reciprocal Identities
            cscθ = 1/sinθ
            secθ = 1/cosθ
            cotθ = 1/tanθ
            sinθ = 1/cscθ
            cosθ = 1/secθ
            tanθ = 1/cotθ

- Pythagorean Identities
            sin²θ+cos²θ=1
            tan²θ+1=sec²θ
            cot²θ+1=csc²θ

- Even/Odd Identities
            sin(-θ)=-sinθ
            cos(-θ)=cosθ
            tan(-θ)=-tanθ
            csc(-θ)=-cscθ
            sec(-θ)=secθ
            cot(-θ)=-cotθ

- Double Angle Identities
            sin(2θ)=2sinθcosθ
            cos(2θ)=cos²θ-sin²θ
            =2cos²θ-1
            =1-2sin²θ

            tan(2θ) = 2tanθ / 1-tan²θ

- Half Angle Identities
            sin(θ/2) = ± √1-cosθ/2
            cos(θ/2) = ± √1+cosθ/2
            tan(θ/2) = ± √1-cosθ/1+cosθ

- Product to Sum Identities
            sin α sin ß = 1/2[cos(α-ß)-cos(α+ß)]
            cos α cos ß = 1/2[cos(α-ß)+cos(α+ß)]
            sin α cos ß = 1/2[cos(α+ß)+cos(α-ß)]
            cos α sin ß = 1/2[cos(α+ß)-cos(α-ß)]

- Sum to Product Identities
            sin α + sin ß = 2sin(α+ß/2)cos(α-ß/2)
            sin α - sin ß = 2cos(α+ß/2)sin(α-ß/2)
            cos α + cos ß = 2cos(α+ß/2)cos(α-ß/2)
            cos α - cos ß = -2sin(α+ß/2)sin(α-ß/2)
            

- Sum/Differences Identities
            sin(α±ß) = sinα cosß ± cosα sinß
            cos(α±ß) = cosα cosß ± sinα sinß
            tan(α±ß) = tanα ± tanß / 1 ± tanα tanß

- Mollweide's Formula
            a+b/c = cos[1/2(α-ß)] / sin(1/2γ)

- Periodic Identities
            sin(θ+2πn)=sinθ
            cos(θ+2πn)=cosθ
            tan(θ+πn)=tanθ
            csc(θ+2πn)=cscθ
            sec(θ+2πn)=secθ
            cot(θ+πn)=cotθ

- Law of Cosines
            a²=b²+c²-2bc cos α
            b²=a²+c²-2ac cos ß
            c²=a²+b²-2ab cos γ

- Law of Sines
            sinα/a = sinß/b = sinγ/c

- Law of Tangents
            a-b/a+b = tan[1/2(α-ß)] / tan[1/2(α+ß)]
            b-c/b+c = tan[1/2(ß-γ)] / tan[1/2(ß+γ)]
            a-c/a+c = tan[1/2(α-γ)] / tan[1/2(α+γ)]

- Cofunction Identities
            sin(π/2-θ) = cosθ
            csc(π/2-θ) = secθ
            tan(π/2-θ) = cotθ
            cos(π/2-θ) = sinθ
            sec(π/2-θ) = cscθ
            cot(π/2-θ) = tanθ















